\begin{definition*}[Symmetric strict monoidal category]
    {}
    A \maindef{symmetric strict monoidal category} is a \SY{strict monoidal category} $\tup{\CatC, \mtimescat, \idmoncat}$ which is also a symmetric stacking category.
    This means that $\CatC$ is equipped with braidings
    \begin{equation*}
        \permmap_{\Obja, \Objb} \colon \Obja \mtimescat \Objb \mto \Objb \mtimescat \Obja \end{equation*}
    which satisfy the conditions of naturality, compatibility with nesting, and symmetry.
\end{definition*}
